description: The Karnataka high court will deliver its verdict on Chief Minister Siddaramaiah's petition challenging Governor Thaawar Chand Gehlot's approval for an investigation into his alleged misuse of power in the MUDA site allotment case. An interim order preventing action against Siddaramaiah remains in place until the decision is announced. Both sides presented their arguments before Justice M. Nagaprasanna.
title: Muda case: HC verdict today on Siddaramaiah's plea against governor's probe nod

description: Kapil Dev, former Indian cricket captain, suggests that a cricketer's prime years span from ages 26 to 34, with fitness determining their career length. Using Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli as examples, he notes their retirement from T20Is but continued activity in other formats. Retirement is ultimately a personal decision influenced by fitness and passion for the game.
title: Are Rohit, Virat past their 'prime'? Kapil says 'keep playing as long as...'

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi met Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy in New York to discuss enhancing bilateral relations and cooperation on international platforms like the UN and G20. They focused on implementing the Peace Formula and preparing for a second Peace Summit. Modi reiterated India's commitment to resolving the Ukraine conflict and restoring peace.
title: PM Modi meets Ukraine's Zelenskyy, reaffirms India's support for peaceful resolution

description: Baramulla MP Engineer Rashid accused NC's Omar Abdullah and People's Conference's Sajad Gani Lone of conspiring to defeat his Awami Ittehad Party candidates in the J&K assembly elections. Recently released on interim bail, Rashid denied being a BJP proxy and criticized regional parties for uniting against him.
title: Engineer Rashid accuses Omar, Lone of ganging up against him

description: In the second phase of J&K assembly elections, 65 out of 238 candidates have criminal cases against them, including serious charges for some. Only a small percentage are women. Additionally, over half the candidates are crorepatis with an average asset value of Rs 5.80 crore per candidate.
title: 65 of 238 candidates in phase 2 of J&K polls facing criminal cases
Will push for restoration of J&K’s statehood: Rahul Gandhi
In a first, IIM-A introduces quotas for PhD admissions

description: At the UN's 'Summit of the Future', PM Modi stressed the need for reforms in global institutions to foster peace and development. Highlighting India's success in poverty reduction, he expressed readiness to share this experience with the Global South. Modi also emphasized balanced digital governance and collective action against terrorism.
title: Success of humanity doesn't lie in battlefield: PM at UN
Kerala Dubai returnee is India's first Mpox patient with fast-spreading strain

description: The Nepal government's decision to prohibit its Gorkhas from joining Indian Army's seven Gorkha regiments under the Agnipath scheme has severely affected khukuri suppliers in Uttarakhand. With no recruitment of Nepal-domiciled Gorkhas for four years, businesses have faced a 50-60% decline in demand for this iconic weapon, impacting local economies.
title: Khukuri business loses shine as Gorkhas shun Agnipath
End of the road? Trams to run only on ‘heritage route’, state to tell HC
Hilsa for India not a gift, it's an export: Bangladesh

description: Tamil Nadu Governor R N Ravi asserted that secularism is a European concept, not initially part of India's Constitution. He alleged it was introduced during the Emergency by an 'insecure Prime Minister' to placate some sections of society. Congress denounced his comments as outrageous and unacceptable.
title: Secularism European, not Bharatiya concept: TN governor R N Ravi

description: Three senior Andhra Pradesh IPS officers suspended recently on charges of framing, arresting and harassing a Mumbai-based actress earlier this year have been listed as accused in the case along with two other cops and Kukkala Vidyasagar, a YSRCP leader, who has been named prime accused.
title: Andhra IPS trio named accused in actress case
Over 9 in 10 F&O retail traders lose money: Sebi

description: Annu Bediya, a 30-year-old tribal youth from Jharkhand's Ramgarh district, died after collapsing during a 10-km run for an excise constable recruitment test in Sahibganj. This incident raises the death toll linked to the physical test to 16. Authorities are investigating, and his family bore the cost of transporting his body back home.
title: Jharkhand excise staff fitness test claims one more; toll 16

description: A probe into the alleged incident of railway sabotage near Kim in Surat revealed three railway employees had removed parts of the track to make it seem like an attempt to derail a train, took videos and photos, and installed fish plates and other removed parts back, so as to gain acclaim and rewards for averting an accident. Police have arrested three accused & shared details of the probe. Two of them are trackmen.
title: 3 railmen held for cooking up sabotage plot to earn rewards

description: In Sambhal, a 17-year-old girl was murdered by her family who feared she would not testify against her alleged rapist. Initially blamed on the accused rapist out on bail, police investigations revealed that her mother, two brothers, and uncle plotted and executed the crime. CCTV footage helped uncover the truth.
title: Family kills rape survivor, frames 'rapist' out on bail

description: Vodafone Idea Limited has approached the government for relief on its Rs 70,000 crore AGR dues after the Supreme Court rejected its curative petition. The company is working with senior officials and banks to raise debt for network expansion, expecting to secure funding within 7-8 weeks while also engaging new lenders.
title: Vodafone goes back to govt; chairman says that there is a clear...

title: Horoscope today: Read your today's astrological predictions
